gomodel:SYNGO_1007  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The location of the adenosine A1 receptor was assessed by pre-embedding immunoperoxidase and immunogold labelling. The A1 receptor was found in dendrites and spines (Table1 and 2, Fig.2-6). Immunoreactivity was found on plasma membranes, but also on endomembranes.\n\nAn affinity purified polyclonal antiserum was raised against a synthetic rat peptide (aa309-326) in the C-terminus of the receptor. The specificity of the antibody was tested by Western Blot and IHC using wildtype and A1 KO mice (Fig.1).. Experimental description: Six adult male Sprague-Dawleyrats (200-250 g; Taconic Farms, Germantown, NY) weredeeply anesthetized by... The control experiments to test the antibody specificity were performed in mice." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1007" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
